🌐 Computer Networks
1️⃣ How YouTube Streams Video (Real System 🔥)
Simple Idea

YouTube doesn’t send full video at once → it sends small chunks continuously

Mental Model 🎬

Like watching a movie:

you don’t download whole movie
it plays while loading
How It Works
Video divided into chunks
Uses CDN (nearby servers)
Uses UDP (for speed)
Buffer stores upcoming video
Why It Works
reduces buffering
faster playback
scalable
Interview Gold Line ⭐

👉 “Streaming uses chunking + CDN + buffering for smooth playback.”

2️⃣ Why Buffering Happens (Deep Insight)
Simple Idea

Buffering happens when:

👉 Data arrival < playback speed

Mental Model 🚰

Water filling slower than draining → empty tank → pause

Reasons
low bandwidth
high latency
congestion
server delay
Interview Tip

Always explain using:
👉 data rate mismatch

3️⃣ How WhatsApp Sends Messages
Simple Idea

Messages go through central server system

Flow
You send message
Message goes to WhatsApp server
Server sends to receiver
Why Not Direct?

Because:

receiver may be offline
server ensures delivery
Protocol Used
TCP → reliability
encryption → security
Mental Model

Post office system 📬

Key Insight ⭐

👉 “Server acts as mediator”

4️⃣ Client-Server vs Peer-to-Peer
Client-Server
central server
example: WhatsApp, websites
Peer-to-Peer (P2P)
direct communication
example: torrent
Mental Model
Client-server → teacher in class
P2P → students sharing notes
Why Both Exist
client-server → control
P2P → scalability
Memory Trick

Server = central
P2P = direct

